OL,6,FShe rose to prominence in 2018 with
OL,7,Fher memoir Somebody I Used To Know,
OL,8,Fwhich she followed up four years later
OL,9,Fwith What I Wish I Knew About Dementia.
OL,11,FShe was a vocal advocate for assisted
OL,12,Fdying before her own death at the age
OL,13,Fof 68.
OL,15,FIn her final blog post she wrote:
OL,16,F"Dementia is a cruel disease that
OL,17,Fplays tricks on your very existence.
